parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed braking in wet conditions can lead to increased stopping distances, accidents, and loss of control, posing a significant risk to the driver and other road users.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage or respond slowly (2-3 seconds) when driving in wet conditions
or driving through puddles. The brakes may require repeated pumping or heavy application to start working
and the stopping distance is substantially increased.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to misfire, leading to catalytic converter failure, oxygen sensor damage, and potentially resulting in engine stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the catalytic converter can lead to engine stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents, as well as costly repairs.
The failure of the thrust bearing can cause the crankshaft to become loose inside the engine block, resulting in engine failure, which can lead to accidents and costly repairs.
The buildup of combustion residue in the intake manifold can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
Engine stalling can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
Oil leaks can cause engine failure, leading to accidents and costly repairs.
The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle stalls when the clutch is pushed at idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loud noises, stalling, and loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: loud noise from transmission in 4th gear from 3500-4000 RPM at full throttle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: full braking unable to stop or turn the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause oil to leak from the rear of the vehicle, leading to a loss of traction and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission during towing can cause the rear wheels to lock up, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.

The failure of the ignition coil pack can cause the engine to misfire, stall, or run rough, leading to decreased performance, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle hesitates or loses power when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing environmental harm.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
the catalytic converter needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle battery can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
